

                                Angular - Front End Technology
                            --------------------------------------
                        
                                       Basic Commands
                                ---------------------------

                    1. to create a project - ng new project-name / ng new project-name --routing

                    2. to run Angular project - ng serve / ng serve --open 

                    3. to generate component - ng g c component-name

                    3. to generate service - ng g s service-name



                                    Basic Building Blocks

                                -----------------------------


                1. Module - To import 3rd party - (root module - AppModule)

                2. Component - To create html,css,ts file (root component - AppComponent)

                3. Data Binding - sharing of data inside component

                    3.1 One way Binding - data shairing only in one direction at a time

                        3.1.1 Component (ts) to View (html)

                            3.1.1.1 String Interpolation - {{expression}}

                            3.1.1.2 Property Binding - [attribute name]="Property name"

                        3.1.2 View (html) to Component (ts)

                            3.1.2.1 Event Binding   (event name)="function-name()"

                            3.1.2.2 Event Binding using $event  (event name)="function-name($event)"

                            3.1.2.3 Using template referencing variable - #variable-name

                    3.2 Two way Binding - data shairing in both direction-
                    
                            3.2.1 ngModel - import FormsModule in AppModule
                            - [(ngModel)]="Property-name" , Property-name should defined in ts file 

                4. Angular routing - to set path for component in appRoutingModule
                    - {path:value,component:class-name} 
                    - use router-outlet selector inside the root component

                5. Dependency Injection- to share data between dependent classes

                6. Angular services - to hold redundant data

                7. ngSubmit 

                8. Angular Directives -  To manupulate DOM

                    8.1 Component Directives 

                    8.2 Structural Directives

                        8.2.1 - *ngFor


                9. Angular Forms

                    9.1 Template Driven Forms - first design html

                    9.2 Model Driven Forms - first design in ts file

                        9.2.1 Reactive Forms - Form group, array , control
                                - Add validations
                                - import ReactiveFormsModule 






